"title": "7031: unity, God's goal of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7031: unity, god's goal of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's purpose is to bring together and reconcile to himself the whole of creation. This desire for unity is a reflection of the unity within the Godhead; it is expressed in marriage, and demonstrated in the fellowship of the church.</p>\n<h2>Unity is a reflection of God's person</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4\">DEU 6:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:22\">JHN 17:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:29\">MRK 12:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:32\">MRK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1\">JHN 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11\">JHN 17:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:20\">GAL 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:7\">1JN 5:7</a></p>\n<h2>Alienation is a result of sin</h2>\n<h3>Alienation from God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:8\">GEN 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:23-Gen3:24\">GEN 3:23–3:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:2\">ISA 59:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:16\">EZK 28:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:4\">JAS 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>Alienation from one another</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:7-Gen4:9\">GEN 4:7–4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:23-Gen4:24\">GEN 4:23–4:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:11\">GEN 6:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:1-Jas4:2\">JAS 4:1–4:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:19\">JUD 1:19</a></p>\n<h2>God's purpose in unity</h2>\n<h3>To bring together all peoples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps133:1\">PSA 133:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9-Eph1:10\">EPH 1:9–1:10</a></strong></p>\n<h3>To unite all peoples under his rule</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:10\">GEN 49:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:8-Ps72:11\">PSA 72:8–72:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:4\">ISA 2:2–2:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:3\">MIC 4:1–4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:9-Phil2:11\">PHP 2:9–2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:15\">REV 11:15</a></p>\n<h3>To unite all peoples in worship</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:23-Isa19:25\">ISA 19:23–19:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:9\">PSA 86:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa56:6-Isa56:8\">ISA 56:6–56:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:20-Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:20–8:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:16\">ZEC 14:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:17\">MRK 11:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:4\">REV 15:4</a></p>\n<h3>To bring reconciliation between Jew and Gentile</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:11-Eph2:19\">EPH 2:11–2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa14:1\">ISA 14:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom10:12\">ROM 10:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:28\">GAL 3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:11\">COL 3:11</a></p>\n<h3>To bring reconciliation among his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:4\">JER 50:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:10-Isa11:13\">ISA 11:10–11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:21-Ezek37:24\">EZK 37:21–37:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:12\">MIC 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:24\">MAT 5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:2\">PHP 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>To reconcile humanity to himself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19-Col1:22\">COL 1:19–1:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:10-Rom5:11\">ROM 5:10–5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:18-2Cor5:19\">2CO 5:18–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:19-Heb10:20\">HEB 10:19–10:20</a></p>\n<h2>Expressions of unity brought by God</h2>\n<h3>Unity between husband and wife</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:24\">GEN 2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:15\">MAL 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:5-Matt19:6\">MAT 19:5–19:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:7-Mark10:8\">MRK 10:7–10:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:16\">1CO 6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:4\">1CO 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:10-1Cor7:11\">1CO 7:10–7:11</a></p>\n<h3>Marriage as an expression of unity between God and his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:2\">JER 2:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:31-Eph5:32\">EPH 5:31–5:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:5\">ISA 54:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:32\">JER 31:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:16\">HOS 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:29\">JHN 3:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:7\">REV 19:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:9\">REV 21:9</a></p>\n<h3>Unity within the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:21\">JHN 17:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:1\">ACT 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:32\">ACT 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:10\">1CO 1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:17\">1CO 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:13\">EPH 4:13</a></p>",
